-Steps to Mount a Volume/Directory from Host to Docker Container in Azure
-Access Azure Portal: Log in to the Azure portal and navigate to "Virtual Machines."
-Select VM: Choose the virtual machine running the Docker container.
-Attach Disk: Go to the "Disks" section, select or attach a new disk, and configure its settings.
-Prepare Disk: Connect to the VM, initialize, and format the disk to make it usable.
-Mount Disk: Mount the disk to a directory on the host system.
-Run Docker with Volume: Use the docker run command with the -v flag to mount the host directory to a path in the container. Example: docker run -v /host/path:/container/path.
-Verify Mount: Check inside the container to confirm the directory is properly mounted and accessible.
